
Base Line Data Model Scatch 

Baseline Data Model Sketch
You need a simple, analytical-friendly ER design. Core entities:

publications

pk: publication_id (auto-int)
doi (string, unique)
title (string)
publisher (string)
container_title (journal or conference name)
type (article, book-chapter, etc.)
issued_date (date)

authors

pk: author_id
given_name, family_name
affiliation

publication_authors (many-to-many bridge)

fk: publication_id
fk: author_id
sequence (order in author list)

sources 

pk: source_id
source_name, issn

dates (if you want a standalone date dimension)

pk: date_id
year, month, day

SQL-normalize:

sql
-- publications table
CREATE TABLE publications (
  publication_id PRIMARY KEY,
  doi TEXT ,
  title TEXT,
  publisher TEXT,
  container_title TEXT,
  type TEXT,
  issued_date DATE
);

-- authors table
CREATE TABLE authors (
  author_id  PRIMARY KEY,
  given_name TEXT,
  family_name TEXT,
  affiliation TEXT
);

-- publication_authors
CREATE TABLE publication_authors (
  publication_id INT REFERENCES publications,
  author_id INT REFERENCES authors,
  sequence INT,
  PRIMARY KEY (publication_id, author_id)
);
